cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper deals with adversarial machine learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The use of autoencoders and their transferability make it likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also deals with the security aspect of machine learning, which makes it relevant to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The use of adversarial training and the focus on robustness make it relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
